    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> to the pan with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>umami seasoning</strong></p><p>Add 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the mushrooms are cooked and the sauce has thickened to a ragù-like consistency</p>",
